Contradict fact: The claim that Americans rallied to elect Philippine president Duterte as their leader is contradicted by the fact that the image has been doctored from a photo of an anti-government protest in Washington DC in 2009.
Exaggerate: The claim exaggerates the support for Duterte by presenting a doctored image as evidence of Americans rallying for him.
Understate: There is no evidence of understatement in this claim.
Falters at times: The claim falters at times by presenting a misleading image and misrepresenting it as support for Duterte.
Lack enough support: The claim lacks enough support as it relies on a doctored image and does not provide any additional evidence of Americans rallying for Duterte.
Problematic assumption: The claim assumes that the image represents genuine support for Duterte, when in reality it has been manipulated.
Exist alternative explanation: The alternative explanation is that the image is from an anti-government protest in Washington DC in 2009 and has been doctored to falsely suggest support for Duterte.
